# HW6: Lighting with Textures

**Author:** Meghasrivardhan P

**Used Faculty Code:** Willem A. Schreuder's CSCIx229 library as base
**Made Changes to:** hw6.c, projection.c
**Used AI in the parts of:** hw6.c (Stone Boulder), Plane.c, FrontPlane.c

**Textures Applied:** Ground, walls, roof, tree bark, tree leaves, table surfaces, table legs, car body, boulder, grenade, airplane, human clothing (shirt, pants, shoes), target pole, target board, house door, healthkit box

**Time Spent:** ~ 1-2 days

## Controls

### Basic Navigation

| Key      | Function                                                 |
| -------- | -------------------------------------------------------- |
| `ESC`    | Exit program                                             |
| `0`      | Reset view angle                                         |
| `x/X`    | Toggle coordinate axes display                           |
| `arrows` | Change view angle (normal mode) / Move camera (FPP mode) |

### Camera Modes

| Key   | Function                                             |
| ----- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| `f/F` | Toggle First-Person Perspective (FPP) mode           |
| `p/P` | Switch between Perspective and Orthogonal projection |

#### First-Person Controls (FPP Mode)

- `↑` : Move forward
- `↓` : Move backward
- `←` : Turn left
- `→` : Turn right

### Zoom & Field of View

| Key | Function                |
| --- | ----------------------- | ------- |
| `-` | Zoom out (increase dim) | (- key) |
| `=` | Zoom in (decrease dim)  | (+ key) |
| `z` | Decrease field of view  |
| `Z` | Increase field of view  |

### Lighting Controls

| Key   | Function                        |
| ----- | ------------------------------- |
| `l/L` | Toggle lighting on/off          |
| `m/M` | Toggle automatic light movement |
| `[`   | Lower light elevation           |
| `]`   | Raise light elevation           |
| `F1`  | Toggle smooth/flat shading      |

#### Light Properties

| Key   | Function                         |
| ----- | -------------------------------- |
| `a/A` | Decrease/increase ambient light  |
| `d/D` | Decrease/increase diffuse light  |
| `s/S` | Decrease/increase specular light |
| `e/E` | Decrease/increase emission light |
| `n/N` | Decrease/increase shininess      |

### Object Scaling

Each object can be individually scaled up or down:

| Object         | Decrease | Increase |
| -------------- | -------- | -------- |
| Human          | `h`      | `H`      |
| Tree           | `t`      | `T`      |
| House          | `y`      | `Y`      |
| Car            | `c`      | `C`      |
| Table          | `b`      | `B`      |
| Target         | `g`      | `G`      |
| Boulder (Rock) | `r`      | `R`      |
| Grenade        | `j`      | `J`      |
| Health-kit     | `k`      | `K`      |
| Wrecked-Plane  | `w`      | `W`      |
| Front-plane    | `q`      | `Q`      |

### Display Modes

| Key | Function                               |
| --- | -------------------------------------- |
| `o` | Cycle through display modes (forward)  |
| `O` | Cycle through display modes (backward) |

#### Available Display Modes

0. **All Objects** - Complete scene with all elements
1. **House Only** - Isolated cabin view
2. **Tree Only** - Single tree display
3. **Ground Only** - Just the terrain
4. **Target Only** - Archery target isolated
5. **Human Only** - Character
6. **Broken Table Only** - Damaged furniture piece
7. **Old Car Only** - Abandoned vehicle
8. **Boulder Only** - Single rock formation
9. **Grenade Only** - Military equipment
10. **Health-kit Only** - Medical supplies (animated rotation)
11. **Wrecked Plane Only** - Crashed aircraft
12. **Front-plane Only** - Front section of the aircraft
